          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "P-LI7"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron beams were produced via the",
                "7Li(p,n)7Be reaction, with a 1.875-MHz pulsed proton",
                "beam.The neutron production target was composed of",
                "thin LiF on a tantalum backing.Target thickness was",
                "chosen such that 2.25-MeV protons would lose",
                "approximately 50 keV before exiting the",
                "target.Neutrons were collimated by a copper shield,",
                "with a 6.35cm opening and a 50.8cm thickness. The",
                "beam was additionally defined by a wax collimator",
                "with an opening matched to that of the copper shield",
                "and tapered down to a 2.2cm opening."
              ]
            }
          ],
